@ganmacs it actually looks like this is sort of a bug in the way the test is currently set up, but it should be simple to fix.

Currently, we are compiling `protoc` when running the [rake-based set of ruby unit tests](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/tools/run_tests/helper_scripts/run_ruby.sh#L22), but we should actually be doing that within the [formal build setup](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/tools/run_tests/run_tests.py#L900) of the ruby tests, which are guaranteed to [run before each of the unit test sets](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/tools/run_tests/run_tests.py#L876).

Can you please move the `make grpc_ruby_plugin` into that "build" script... things should work then, thanks
